
1. How do you upload multiple files in Streamlit?

st.file_uploader(accept_multiple_files=True) returns list of UploadedFile objects:

python
import streamlit as st
import pandas as pd
from io import BytesIO

# Enable multiple file upload (200MB total limit)
uploaded_files = st.file_uploader(
    "Upload datasets", 
    type=['csv', 'xlsx', 'xls'],
    accept_multiple_files=True,
    help="CSV/Excel files only. Max 50MB per file."
)

st.info(f"📁 {len(uploaded_files) if uploaded_files else 0} files selected")

UploadedFile Object Properties:

text
• name (str): Original filename
• type (str): MIME type  
• size (int): Bytes
• read(): Binary content stream
• getvalue(): Full bytes
• seek(0): Reset stream position



2. How can you differentiate between CSV and Excel files after upload?

Runtime file type detection using MIME types + extensions:

python
def detect_file_type(uploaded_file):
    """Production-grade file type validation"""
    mime_type = uploaded_file.type
    filename = uploaded_file.name.lower()
    
    if mime_type == 'text/csv' or filename.endswith('.csv'):
        return 'csv'
    elif mime_type in ['application/vnd.ms-excel', 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet']:
        return 'excel'
    else:
        raise ValueError(f"Unsupported file type: {mime_type}")

# Processing loop with type checking
all_dataframes = []
for uploaded_file in uploaded_files:
    file_type = detect_file_type(uploaded_file)
    
    if file_type == 'csv':
        df = pd.read_csv(uploaded_file)
        st.success(f"✅ CSV loaded: {uploaded_file.name} ({len(df)} rows)")
    elif file_type == 'excel':
        df = pd.read_excel(uploaded_file)
        st.success(f"✅ Excel loaded: {uploaded_file.name} ({len(df)} rows)")
    
    all_dataframes.append((uploaded_file.name, df))


